snippet.textDisplay: Okay so for those who don't know this song is based on the family of marvi so like marvi was a beautiful girl belonged to thar Sindh Pakistan (also thar is in India as well and both Pakistani  and Indian thar are same just partitioned moreover I guess there is no border in between them so but this story is specifically about Pakistani thar) so umar who was king of umarkot (it is located in sindh but some miles away from thar) saw marvi while she was fetching water out from well and he was bewitched by her beauty he took her by force with him to umarkot where he kept her for I guess 10 years offered her all the riches and wanted her to accept him however she kept asking for her family and would never accept him just ask for her family even though marvi was poor but she loved her family so much that even the riches of umar the king did not lure her, she became sick and wouldn't accept umar ina the love of her family that umar the king was so much pressurized that he gave up on his love and left her. So now this song is basically about the joy of her family that they are saying “aayi aayi” these are sindhi words which means “she came back” and when the peacock is entering it's actually representing marvi this story always gives me goosebumps shah abdul latif bhittai the really famous and respectable poet of Sindh has most of his poetry based on them and he also says “ muhnje marowaran ja kapra mera par dil na mera” means “the clothes of my people may be dirty but not their hearts” here he is basically representing the point of view of marvi. However, for umar the king, this is considered an incomplete love story of umar and marvi there is also umerkot fort located in umarkot and it's really beautiful. Furthermore respect to coke studio who has made this song coke studio never fails to revive the different cultures of Pakistan, great work keep it up ❤️💝 💖
